Resistant and susceptible nematode-infected faba bean plants in pots were used, together with a story board explaining in simple terms the methodology of the project, to explain how resistance to stem nematode is being introduced into improved faba bean material for deployment in commercial faba bean breeding.</gtr:impact><gtr:partOfOfficialScheme>false</gtr:partOfOfficialScheme><gtr:primaryAudience>Industry/Business</gtr:primaryAudience><gtr:year>2011</gtr:year></gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:description>Lecture to the Association of Secondary Teachers Annual Conference</gtr:description><gtr:form>A talk or presentation</gtr:form><gtr:geographicReach>National</gtr:geographicReach><gtr:id>35680BD6-E9F2-4D61-A494-C250350F5C76</gtr:id><gtr:impact>&amp;quot;Frontiers&amp;quot; lecture to the Annual Conference of the Association for Science Education - the main UK association for professional science teachers in secondary level education by Prof Donal O'Sullivan. Lecture entitled: &amp;quot;Using peas and beans in the classroom to teach Mendel's Laws, the ntirogen cycle, sustainability and more&amp;quot; accompanied by living demonstration of Mendel's peas.</gtr:impact><gtr:partOfOfficialScheme>false</gtr:partOfOfficialScheme><gtr:primaryAudience>Professional Practitioners</gtr:primaryAudience><gtr:url>https://www.ase.org.uk/documents/ac15-resource-using-peas-and-beans-to-teach-mendels-laws/association-for-science-education-2015-peas-in-the-classroom-weblr.pdf</gtr:url><gtr:year>2015</gtr:year></gtr:disseminationOutput></gtr:disseminationOutputs><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs><gtr:furtherFundingOutput><gtr:amountPounds>707773</gtr:amountPounds><gtr:country>United Kingdom of Great Britain &amp; Northern Ireland (UK)</gtr:country><gtr:currCode>GBP</gtr:currCode><gtr:currCountryCode>United Kingdom</gtr:currCountryCode><gtr:currLang>en_GB</gtr:currLang><gtr:description>Global Challenges Research Fund Foundation Awards for Global 